**Claim 1:** The compounding innovation velocity model suggests that early patent filings are disproportionately valuable — not because the early innovations are better, but because they ENABLE all subsequent innovations. Filing App 1 (123 innovations) was the seed that produced Apps 2-8 (1,766 innovations) plus 114 unfiled. The early filing is the root of the compound.

**Claim 2:** The architectural coupling constant k is itself an innovation. The DESIGN of the system to be composable — consistent principles, modular architecture, constitutional constraints, explicit naming — is a meta-innovation that accelerates all subsequent innovation.

**Claim 3:** The AI collaboration workflow that amplifies k should be documented as a method patent. The specific process — Founder insight → AI architecture → AI implementation → AI validation → AI audit — is a reproducible innovation methodology.

**Claim 4:** The Crown Jewel density metric (structural innovations as a percentage of total output) is a leading indicator of future innovation velocity. Tracking this metric allows prediction of when the compounding curve will steepen (high density) or plateau (low density).

