## Appendix A: Mathematical Notation

**Variables:**
- E = initial cash entry ($)
- s = worker share (0.833 in LB)
- p = platform share (0.167 in LB)
- r = recirculation rate (fraction of Credits respent internally)
- v = velocity (turns per month)
- n = number of turns modeled
- c = cross-scenario flow rate
- M = effective multiplier

**Single-scenario multiplier:**
$$M = \sum_{k=0}^{n-1} s \cdot (s \cdot r)^k = s \cdot \frac{1 - (s \cdot r)^n}{1 - s \cdot r}$$

**Combined multiplier (K scenarios):**
$$M_{combined} = \sum_{i=1}^{K} w_i \cdot M_i + c \cdot \sum_{i \neq j} w_i \cdot w_j \cdot M_{cross}$$

Where w_i = weight of scenario i (proportion of total entry), M_cross = additional turns generated by cross-scenario flow.

**Housing WaterWheel growth:**
$$P(t) = P_0 \cdot (1 + g)^{t/T}$$

Where P(t) = number of properties at time t, P_0 = initial property count, g = surplus growth rate per property, T = time to acquire next property from surplus.

