### What If Your Resume Was Just... What You Did?

Imagine a world where getting a manufacturing partnership didn't require a business plan, a pitch deck, three reference letters, and a six-month approval process.

Instead, you just... did the work.

You see a broken button on a website. You click it. A gold coin flips on screen — you just earned your first Mark.

You find a typo. Click. Coin. Mark.

You notice a layout that looks wrong. You don't just click — you write down what's wrong and how to fix it. Bigger coin. More Marks.

Now you're hooked. You've been playing this game for a week. Your Marks are piling up. Then you notice: "Your Marks are decaying. Lock them in for $5/year."

Five bucks. You're in. Now your Marks are real — backed by a portfolio of patents, permanent, usable.

A month later, you see a bounty: "3D print this canister sleeve and test the twist-lock fit. 75 Marks." You have a printer. You do it. Coin. Marks.

At 500 Marks, something changes. You're a Contractor now. You get first pick on new bounties. Your Marks earn 1.5x. Monthly check-ins with the team.

At 2,000 Marks, you're a Partner. Revenue share on products you helped build. Your name on the product. A Factory Node seed — you could run a small manufacturing operation from your garage.

**You never filled out an application. You never had an interview. You never negotiated a contract.**

You just did the work. The Marks ledger was your resume. The threshold was your interview. The revenue share was your contract.

**DO THE WORK = GET THE STATUS.**

A teenager printing test pieces can reach Partner faster than an engineer who fills out a form and stops.

That's not a slogan. That's the system.

